commit.message:
command-not-found: reduce the amount of search paths

it does not make sense to search $USER/.local/bin or
/usr/local/bin. We know packages don't install there.

It also doesn't make sense to search specific bin directories
for packages such as wine/opencascade/llvm/clang since these
directories only become part of PATH if they are already
installed.

Nor does it make sense to search /var/lib/snapd/snap/bin
we have other code for that.

Reducing the amount of paths speeds up the code.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Ammerlaan <andrewammerlaan@gentoo.org>
